2 (a) (1) Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, by regulation, the
3 Department shall establish and collect a fee to be paid by a generator of coal combustion
4 by–products[, based on a].
5 (2) THE BASE FEE ESTABLISHED BY THE DEPARTMENT UNDER THIS
6 SUBSECTION MAY NOT BE LESS THAN $2.30 per ton [rate] of coal combustion
7 by–products generated by the generator annually.
8 (b) The Department shall base the fees on the following factors:
9 (1) The total annual tonnage of coal combustion by–products that the
10 generator generates;
11 (2) The type and volume of coal combustion by–products generated by the
12 generator;
13 (3) Whether the generator uses or disposes of the coal combustion
14 by–products;
15 (4) To the extent that the coal combustion by–products are used rather
16 than disposed of, the types of the uses;
17 (5) Whether the coal combustion by–products are transported for use or
18 disposal out–of–state; [and]
19 (6) THE VOLUME OF COAL COMBUSTION BY–PRODUCTS THAT HAVE
20 BEEN DISPOSED OF AND REMAIN IN LANDFILLS OR OTHER STORAGE UNITS IN THE
21 STATE THAT ARE SUBJECT TO INSPECTION AND MONITORING, NOT INCLUDING COAL
22 COMBUSTION BY–PRODUCTS THAT HAVE BEEN:
23 (I) ADDED TO CEMENT PRODUCTS;
24 (II) USED IN COAL MINE RECLAMATION; OR
25 (III) BENEFICIALLY REUSED IN A MANNER ACCEPTABLE TO THE
26 DEPARTMENT; AND
27 (7) Other factors the Department considers appropriate.
28 (c) The Department may not establish or impose a fee on coal combustion
29 by–products that are:
30 (1) Beneficially used, as the Department determines; or

