4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
5 (a) The Department of the Environment shall:
6 (1) on or before December 1, 2025, update regulations in accordance with §
7 9–283 of the Environment Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act; and
8 (2) on or before October 1, 2026, adopt regulations to implement:
9 (i) the federal Steam Electric Power Generating Effluent guidelines
10 as adopted on May 9, 2024; and
11 (ii) the final rule governing legacy coal combustion residuals as
12 adopted on May 9, 2024.
13 (b) In adopting regulations in accordance with subsection (a)(2)(ii) of this section,
14 the Department of the Environment may amend the regulations as necessary to protect
15 human health and the environment in the State, including:
16 (1) targeting actions at specific locations where coal combustion
17 by–products have been used previously; and
18 (2) expanding the list of chemicals required to be tested beyond those
19 required by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency to include:
20 (i) arsenic;
21 (ii) boron;
22 (iii) cadmium;
23 (iv) hexavalent chromium;
24 (v) radium–226;
25 (vi) selenium;
26 (vii) vanadium; and
27 (viii) other chemicals as determined by the Department of the
28 Environment.

